import { Component } from '@angular/core'; @Component({ selector: 'app-root', templateUrl: './app.component.html', styleUrls: ['./app.component.css'] }) export class AppComponent { title = 'shipment'; }

Bootstrap tab panel example (using nav-pills)

  • Overview
  • Using nav-pills
  • Applying clearfix
  • Background color

Content's background color is the same for the tab

We use the class nav-pills instead of nav-tabs which automatically creates a background color for the tab

We applied clearfix to the tab-content to rid of the gap between the tab and the content

We use css to change the background color of the content to be equal to the tab
